  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PCI&#xD5;s Women Empowered (WE) initiative is a savings-led microfinance program that strategically integrates economic, human and social capital development. WE groups are made up of 15-20 local women who determine their own leadership roles, savings amounts, loan sizes, and individual or group investment decisions. Facilitators train WE groups on savings, financial literacy, bookkeeping, business planning, leadership, and public-speaking. Through the program&#xD5;s leadership development and confidence-building activities, women develop the self-assurance, vision and determination to continue improving their lives and the lives of their families and communities.  WE is active in 12 countries throughout Africa, Asia and the Americas.</narrative>
  </description>
